This paper discusses the comparison of two theorem provers, Isabelle/HOL and Coq, and their features with respect to expressiveness, limitations, and usability. This topic falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) as it deals with formal systems and automated deduction theory. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of theorem proving in solving complex engineering problems, which could also relate to Software Engineering (cs.SE). The comparison of features of the theorem provers could also fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses the use of theorem proving to verify security properties of software systems and algorithms. Finally, the paper's discussion of the theory of automated theorem proving could also relate to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
